```
 Am I right in saying that the capabilities are defined in access.php and that they only give defined users permission to take,change and manage attendance? And if so would you agree that the same permissions should be given for grading student's assessments? Any help would really be appreciated. As a little side note, I have not been using the get_string method when I am using a new word, i.e I just write the word in single quotation marks. What are the implications of this? Thanks, Deborah

I've found that easiest way to add programmatically any resource or activity to course is via backup. Just restore backup into a course 
```text
//restore course from template
$destdir = $CFG->
dataroot
.'/temp/backup/'.md5($course->shortname);
$zipfile = $CFG->dataroot.'/course_templates/backup_file.mbz';
if(file_exists($zipfile)){
	define('CLI_SCRIPT', true);
	require_once($CFG->
dirroot
.'/backup/util/includes/restore_includes.php');
	$packer = new zip_packer();
	$packer->extract_to_pathname($zipfile, $destdir);

	// Transaction
	$transaction = $DB->start_delegated_transaction();
	// Restore backup into course
	$controller = new restore_controller(md5($course->shortname), $course->id, backup::INTERACTIVE_NO, backup::MODE_SAMESITE, 2, backup::TARGET_CURRENT_ADDING);
	$controller->execute_precheck();
	$controller->execute_plan();
	// Commit
	$transaction->allow_commit();
	define('CLI_SCRIPT', false);

	$mods = unserialize($course->modinfo);
	//here you can edit and resource or activity

	rebuild_course_cache($course->id, true);
}
```
 Hope this helps you.

I see new table for settings: CREATE TABLE `prefix_attendance_settings` ( `id` int(3) NOT NULL auto_increment, `acronym` char(2) NOT NULL default '', `descr` varchar(15) NOT NULL default '', `operation` char(1) NOT NULL default '',
PRIMARY KEY ( `id` )
) COMMENT='Attendance settings' AUTO_INCREMENT=5 ; I think about future grade possibilities... In this case we should add few fields: courseid, grade. Global settings should use courseid=0 and was default for any course but each teacher can change it for its own course.

In case of using site wide SSL for Moodle, there is a problem in 'blocks/attendance/tabs.php' line 38. 
```text
if(empty($CFG->loginhttps)) {
 $
wwwroot
 = $CFG->wwwroot;
} else {
 $wwwroot = str_replace('http','https',$CFG->wwwroot);
}
```
 When $wwwroot contains 'https', this script replaces it into 'httpss'. So, please modify that line to 
```text
$wwwroot = str_replace('http:', 'https:', $CFG->wwwroot);
.
```
